---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Capital Gains Harvesting Guide",
  "description": "Learn how to harvest capital gains at a 0% tax rate. Understand income thresholds, timing, and optimal strategies for FIRE.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "FireMaths"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is tax gain harvesting?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Tax gain harvesting is the process of selling taxable investments that have increased in value when your income is low enough to qualify for the 0% long-term capital gains tax bracket, allowing you to reset your cost basis tax-free."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is there a wash sale rule for tax gain harvesting?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, the wash sale rule only applies to selling investments at a loss. You can sell an asset for a gain and immediately buy the exact same asset back to step up your cost basis."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the 0% long-term capital gains bracket for 2024?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For 2024, the 0% bracket goes up to $47,025 for single filers and $94,050 for married filing jointly. When adding the standard deduction, you can realize even more total income before paying capital gains tax."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};

export const meta = {
  title: "Capital Gains Harvesting Guide",
  description: "Learn how to harvest capital gains at a 0% tax rate to permanently increase your cost basis. Includes income thresholds, examples, and step-by-step strategy.",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="firemaths"
  title="Capital Gains Harvesting Guide"
  description="How to harvest capital gains at a 0% tax rate to permanently increase your cost basis."
  canonical="https://firemaths.info/capital-gains-harvesting-guide"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Capital Gains Harvesting Guide</h1>
      <p>Lock in your investment gains completely tax-free.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>0% Capital Gains Calculator (2024)</h2>
      <p>Enter your expected ordinary income to see how much room you have in the 0% long-term capital gains bracket.</p>

      <div class="calculator-form">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="filingStatus">Filing Status</label>
          <select id="filingStatus">
            <option value="single">Single</option>
            <option value="mfj">Married Filing Jointly</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="ordinaryIncome">Expected Ordinary Income (W2, Interest, Non-Qual Dividends)</label>
          <div class="input-prefix">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="ordinaryIncome" value="30000" min="0" step="1000" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <button id="calcBtn" class="calc-btn">Calculate Harvesting Room</button>
      </div>

      <div class="results" id="results" style="display:none;">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0">Tax-Free Gains You Can Harvest:</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent-color); margin: 0.5rem 0;" id="harvestAmount">$0</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">This includes the standard deduction. If you sell and rebuy assets with this amount of long-term gains, you permanently increase your cost basis and owe $0 in federal capital gains taxes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card content-section">
      <h2>The Mechanics of Capital Gains Harvesting</h2>
      <p>As detailed in our <a href="/tax-optimization-fire-guide">Tax Optimization FIRE Guide</a>, harvesting capital gains is one of the most powerful strategies available to early retirees living on a modest taxable income.</p>

      <h3>How it Works</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Identify assets in your taxable brokerage account that have long-term capital gains (held for &gt; 1 year).</li>
        <li>Ensure your ordinary income plus these gains keeps you under the 0% bracket limit.</li>
        <li>Sell the assets.</li>
        <li>Immediately buy the exact same assets back.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Unlike Tax-Loss Harvesting, there is <strong>no wash-sale rule for gains</strong>. You do not have to wait 30 days to buy back the same index fund.</p>

      <h3>Why do this?</h3>
      <p>By selling and rebuying, you are raising your "cost basis" (what the IRS considers your purchase price) for free. When you eventually sell those shares years later when your income might be higher, you will owe significantly less tax because you already locked in a portion of the gains at a 0% rate.</p>

      <h3>State Taxes Warning</h3>
      <p>While the federal government offers a 0% rate for long-term capital gains, many state governments do not. If your state taxes capital gains as ordinary income, harvesting gains will generate a state tax bill. Always factor state taxes into your mathematical optimization.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const config2024 = {
      single: {
        stdDeduction: 14600,
        zeroPercentLimit: 47025
      },
      mfj: {
        stdDeduction: 29200,
        zeroPercentLimit: 94050
      }
    };

    document.getElementById('calcBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
      const status = document.getElementById('filingStatus').value;
      const ordinaryIncome = parseFloat(document.getElementById('ordinaryIncome').value) || 0;

      const config = config2024[status];

      // Standard deduction offsets ordinary income first.
      // Whatever standard deduction is left offsets capital gains.
      const taxableOrdinaryIncome = Math.max(0, ordinaryIncome - config.stdDeduction);

      // The 0% limit applies to total taxable income (Ordinary + Capital Gains).
      // So the room left in the 0% bracket is the limit minus taxable ordinary income.
      let harvestRoom = config.zeroPercentLimit - taxableOrdinaryIncome;

      if (harvestRoom < 0) harvestRoom = 0;

      document.getElementById('harvestAmount').innerText = '$' + harvestRoom.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0});
      document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'block';
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .hero p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }
    .calculator-form {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .input-group {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .input-prefix {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .input-prefix span {
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .input-prefix input, select {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border: none;
      background: transparent;
      color: inherit;
      font-size: 1rem;
      outline: none;
    }
    select {
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      background: #111;
      padding: 0.6rem;
    }
    .calc-btn {
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: #000;
      border: none;
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      transition: opacity 0.2s;
    }
    .calc-btn:hover {
      opacity: 0.9;
    }
    .results {
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      text-align: center;
    }
    .content-section h2, .content-section h3 {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .content-section p, .content-section li {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    a {
      color: var(--accent-color);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
